'''Anas Saeed Badawi''' ({{langx|ar|أنس بدوي}}; born 13 September 1997) is a [[Jordan]]ian professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Jordanian Pro League]] club [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
===Al-Ahli===
Badawi began his career at [[Al Ahli SC (Amman)|Al-Ahli]], rising through the club's ranks.<ref name="Kooora">{{cite web |title=أنس بدوي في حوار لكووورة: المربع الذهبي هدف الجزيرة |url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B3-%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%8A-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D9%84%D9%83%D9%88%D9%88%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B0%D9%87%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9/1391903 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=26 February 2025}}</ref>

====Sahab (loan)====
Badawi was a part of the [[Sahab SC|Sahab]] squad that gained promotion in the [[2019 Jordan League Division 1|2019 Jordanian First Division League]].<ref name="Kooora"/>

===Shabab Al-Aqaba===
Badawi joined [[Shabab Al-Aqaba SC|Shabab Al-Aqaba]] during the [[2021 Jordanian Pro League]] season and remained at the club for three season, being a major contributor during his time at the club.<ref name="Kooora"/>

===Al-Jazeera===
Badawi joined [[Al-Jazeera SC (Amman)|Al-Jazeera]] during the [[2024–25 Jordanian Pro League]], establishing himself as a key player for the club with a goal and three assists.<ref name="Kooora"/><ref>{{cite web |title=الجزيرة يكتسح شباب العقبة بسداسية |url=https://www.kooora.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AD-%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%B3%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A9/1373313 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=7 December 2024}}</ref>

===Al-Faisaly===
On 20 May 2025, Badawi joined [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] on a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يعزز صفوفه بتعاقدات جديدة استعدادًا للموسم الكروي 2025-2026 |url=https://www.almamlakatv.com/news/169446-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%B2-%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%88%D9%81%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8B%D8%A7-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%8A-20252026 |website=almamlakatv.com |publisher=Al-Mamlaka |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=20 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يعلن عن صفقات نارية استعدادًا للموسم المقبل |url=https://royanews.tv/news/349658 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> He joined the club due to its special status within [[Football in Jordan|Jordan]] and his admiration to the fanbase.<ref>{{cite web |title=بدوي: تمثيل الفيصلي حلم كل لاعب.. وإدارة الحسين تواصلت معي |url=https://menafn.com/arabic/1109602875/%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%AD%D9%84%D9%85-%D9%83%D9%84-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%95%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B5%D9%84%D8%AA-%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%8A |website=menafn.com |publisher=MENA FN |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=27 May 2025}}</ref> He was sent off on his debut against his former club [[Al-Jazeera SC (Amman)|Al-Jazeera]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zaki |first1=Mohab |title=بعشرة لاعبين.. الفيصلي يخطف فوزًا مثيرًا من الجزيرة في افتتاح الدوري الأردني 2026-25 |url=https://www.mercatotime.com/live-score/jordan-premier-league-round-1-al-faisaly-vs-al-jazeera/ |website=mercatotime.com |publisher=Mercato Time |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=2 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 24 August 2025, Badawi was called-up to the [[Jordan national under-23 football team|Jordan national team]] to participate in [[Exhibition game#International football|friendly]] matches against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] and [[Dominican Republic national football team|Dominican Republic]], becoming one of four players to enter the national team for the first time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=4 لاعبين يدخلون قائمة منتخب الأردن للمرة الأولى |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/4-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%89 |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWin |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=24 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الأردن يدخل معسكراً بقيادة السلامي قبل مواجهة روسيا والدومينكان |url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/sport/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%AE%D9%84-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%B3%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%8B-%D8%A8%D9%82%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%84-%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A9-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86 |website=alaraby.co.uk |publisher=The New Arab |access-date=25 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=24 August 2025}}</ref>

